A game of Plinko is played by dropping a ball at the top-middle of a set of pegs. Each time the ball hits a peg, it has a $\frac{1}{2}$ probability of deflecting either to the left or to the right. What is the probability that the ball lands in the middle slot as shown in the diagram (the red line)? [asy]
size(3inch, 2.25inch);
for (int i = 0; i < 8; i += 2) {

draw(circle((0, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((2, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((4, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((6, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((8, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((10, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((12, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((14, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((16, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((1, i), 0.1));

draw(circle((3, i), 0.1));

draw(circle((5, i), 0.1));

draw(circle((7, i), 0.1));

draw(circle((9, i), 0.1));

draw(circle((11, i), 0.1));

draw(circle((13, i), 0.1));

draw(circle((15, i), 0.1));
}

pen target = red + linewidth(2);

draw((-0.8, -1)--(0.8, -1));
draw((1.2, -1)--(2.8, -1));
draw((3.2, -1)--(4.8, -1));
draw((5.2, -1)--(6.8, -1));
draw((7.2, -1)--(8.8, -1), target);
draw((9.2, -1)--(10.8, -1));
draw((11.2, -1)--(12.8, -1));
draw((13.2, -1)--(14.8, -1));
draw((15.2, -1)--(16.8, -1));

pen tube = black + linewidth(2);
draw((7.2, 9)--(7.2, 7.8)--(8.8, 7.8)--(8.8, 9), tube);

filldraw(Circle((8, 8.5), 0.6), blue);
[/asy]

In the diagram below, lines $k$ and $\ell$ are parallel.  Find the measure of angle $x$ in degrees. [asy]
size(200);
import markers;
pair A = dir(-22)*(0,0);
pair B = dir(-22)*(4,0);
pair C = dir(-22)*(4,2);
pair D = dir(-22)*(0,2);
pair F = dir(-22)*(0,1.3);
pair G = dir(-22)*(4,1.3);
pair H = dir(-22)*(2,1);
pair I = dir(-22)*(1.35,1.3);

markangle(Label("$x$",Relative(0.5)),n=1,radius=11,I+B,I,(2*I-B));

pair X,Y;

X=A;
Y=B;
draw(1.3*X-.3*Y--1.3*Y-.3*X);

X=A;
Y=C;
draw(1.3*X-.3*Y--1.3*Y-.3*X);

X=C;
Y=B;
draw(1.3*X-.3*Y--1.3*Y-.3*X);

X=B;
Y=D;
draw(1.3*X-.3*Y--1.3*Y-.3*X);

X=G;
Y=F;
draw(1.3*X-.3*Y--1.3*Y-.3*X);

label("$\ell$",1.4*A-.4*B);
label("$k$",1.4*F-.4*G);

//label("$x$",H+(.4,-.15));
label("$30^\circ$",A+(1,-.1));
label("$90^\circ$",B+(.4,.1));
